---
import BaseLayout from '../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Review Guidelines">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Review Guidelines</h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700">
      <p class="text-lg">Our goal is to help tenants make informed housing decisions. To maintain a trustworthy platform, please follow these guidelines when submitting reviews.</p>

      <section class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-green-800 mb-3">Do Include</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-green-900">
          <li><strong>Your honest experience</strong> - Share what it was actually like living there</li>
          <li><strong>Specific details</strong> - Mention concrete issues like response times, repair quality, or building conditions</li>
          <li><strong>Both positives and negatives</strong> - A balanced review is more helpful and credible</li>
          <li><strong>Relevant timeframe</strong> - Conditions may have changed since you lived there</li>
          <li><strong>Factual information</strong> - Stick to things you personally experienced or witnessed</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-red-800 mb-3">Do Not Include</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-red-900">
          <li><strong>Personal information</strong> - No names, phone numbers, or identifying details about landlords, staff, or neighbors</li>
          <li><strong>Profanity or threats</strong> - Keep language respectful even when describing negative experiences</li>
          <li><strong>Discriminatory content</strong> - No content targeting protected groups</li>
          <li><strong>False statements</strong> - Don't exaggerate or make up issues that didn't happen</li>
          <li><strong>Reviews for places you didn't live</strong> - Only review properties where you were an actual tenant</li>
          <li><strong>Promotional content</strong> - No advertising or spam</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Review Moderation</h2>
        <p>All reviews are checked before being published. Reviews that violate these guidelines will be rejected. You'll receive an email if your review needs changes before it can be published.</p>
        <p class="mt-3">Common reasons for rejection:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 mt-2">
          <li>Contains names or personal information</li>
          <li>Unable to verify tenancy</li>
          <li>Appears to be fake or spam</li>
          <li>Contains threats or harassment</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Landlord Responses</h2>
        <p>Landlords and property managers can claim their properties and respond to reviews. Responses are also moderated and must follow the same guidelines about respectful language and no personal information.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Disputing a Review</h2>
        <p>If you believe a review is fake or violates our guidelines, please contact us at reviews@ratemyplace.org with the specific review and your concerns. We investigate all reports.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-3">Why This Matters</h2>
        <p class="text-blue-900">Honest reviews help other tenants avoid bad situations and find good homes. They also help good landlords stand out. By following these guidelines, you're contributing to a more transparent rental market that benefits everyone.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
